result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan Jeffrey Paxton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Ryan Jeffrey Paxton in court with attorney Christopher John Ertl.  Defendant Ryan Jeffrey Paxton in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

As to Count 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 31 months in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 42 days served.  Court ordered 13 months Initial Term Of Confinement and 18 months Extended Supervision. Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.  The Court stayed this sentence and placed the defendant on 24 months probation.


CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERIVSION:
-As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction.  This time is stayed pending a review on 1/15/2016.
-Mental Health Evaluation and take ALL prescribed medication, and/or any treatment deemed appropriate.        
-Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
-Maintain absolute sobriety.
-Successfully complete any other counseling and/or treatment deemed appropriate.
-No contact with victim.
-No firearms; weapons.
-Provide a DNA sample.
-Defendant to pay all supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.
-Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.  Case adjourned to Branch 36.
